          "display_name": null,
          "email": "Nathaniel.Potter@intel.com",
          "username": "ntpttr"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-22 23:45:48.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 11:\n\nHi Haibin. I do understand it, but I don't think that adding more flavors with properties will change anything about the flow of code through my new function or really test anything. I don't think that the \"properties\" member of the flavor detail exists in newton, or at least I can't find any proof of it. I saw that you also put that into Ocata, but I don't think that it exists in ocata either. https://developer.openstack.org/api-ref/compute/#show-flavor-details\n\nHaving the separate mocked extra specs return value for the call out to extra specs that I make on line 61 of registration.py is the way that I get values. I can add more of those to make the testing more robust if that would help.",
        "patchset_number": 11
      },
      {
        "id": "7616308a0d5c230f2c18f5055b78c0bf01a7c211",
        "author": {
